 <p>I'm trying to adapt some old sample DSP code from a conference to learn Rust generics. I'm having trouble with E0283 - I want the compiler to infer a type but I don't think my trait implementations are correct and this is why I'm seeing the error.</p>
<p>I've pasted the code below with only the necessary parts. I wanted to design the traits so that when I call <code>.process</code> on the Node with an <code>f32</code>, the compiler should know that this is the concrete type for <code>S</code> that I want to provide.</p>
<pre><code>use std::{ops::Add};
use num_traits::Float;

